quote.p:
—to facilitate deployment of effective strategic defenses as
                                    soon as possible, should a decision for such deployments be
                                    taken;

—Both sides would conduct research, development and testing,
                                    which are permitted by the ABM
                                    Treaty through 1992;

—Such discussions would last up to two years. At the end of two
                                    years, either party would have an unfettered right to deploy
                                    advanced strategic defenses;

—While both sides would continue to abide by the ABM Treaty, do not specify broad
                                    or narrow as correct; both sides would agree to disagree on this
                                    during the period;
